The food is not really good compare to other dim sum spots. Waitresses give their friends sitting as priority. So you might wait forever for seats here. They also don't pick up empty plates once you finished your dish.

One of the few best dimsum places in Brooklyn. The quality and service is amazing. Dimsum that's worth the wait. If you want to avoid the crowds, go after 1pm. Same fresh quality. Never left overs. Fyi- shrimp dumplings are a must.

Nice Cantonese style food. Dim Sum are fresh. You have varieties options. It is an excellent place for Dim Sum and dinner.  If you are not sure what dish you would like to choose for dinner, listen to the waiters' suggestion.  They are always busy. Highly suggest reserve your table ahead of time for dinner. If you are not an early bird for Dim Sum, you just have to be patient and wait for your number called.
